
    README for Perl module Template::Plugin::JSON

This module provides a plugin for use with the Template Toolkit.
It provides a .json vmethod to all value types when loaded.
You can also decode a json string back to a data structure.

You can read a nicely formatted version of the documentation for
this module online:

    https://metacpan.org/pod/Template::Plugin::JSON

You should be able to install this using your usual method for installing
modules from CPAN. If you don't have one, have a look at:

    http://www.cpan.org/modules/INSTALL.html

This module was written by Yuval Kogman <nothingmuch@woobling.org>

